\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Once the answer is found, this question is the key to a gate that leads one to a completely different world. It is, at the same time, a slim line that separates those who know from those who don't. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
In the world in which we live, mankind is caught up in a continuous search for the answers to many questions like "what?", "how?" and "in what way?", and can make but little headway in answering them. It is unlikely for man to make his way to the truth un
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 l\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ess he asks himself the question "why?" about the extraordinary order and balance with which he interacts. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 In this book, we will deal with the subject of "the atom", the groundwork of every animate and inanimate thing. After seeing what occurs and in what\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 way it occurs with regards to the atom, we will seek the answers to the question "why?" The answer to this question will take us to the truth we pursue. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Since the first half of the 19th century, hundreds of scientists worked day and night to reveal the s\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
ecrets of the atom. These studies that uncovered the form, motion, structure and other properties of the atom shattered the very grounds of classical physics that assumed matter to be an entity without any beginning or end, and laid the foundation for mod
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 e\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 rn physics. They also produced many questions. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Many physicists, looking for answers to these questions, finally agreed that there is perfect order, unerring balance and conscious design in the atom, as in everything else in the universe. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 This truth is re\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
vealed in the Qur'an sent down by Allah fourteen centuries ago. As made clear in the verses of the Qur'an, the whole universe works in perfect order because the earth, the sky and everything in between is created by Allah, Who has infinite power and wisdo
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 m\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 . 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
It is certainly no wonder that everything created by Allah has extraordinary excellence and runs within a flawless order. What comes as a real surprise is man's unrelenting insensitivity towards the numerous miracles he encounters, sees, hears, and know
