\par }{\f0\fs22\cf1\insrsid3347702\charrsid14289276 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 The atomic bombs dropped in the final year of World War II have revealed to the whole wo\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
rld the tremendous power hidden in the atom. Both bombs caused hundreds of thousands of people to lose their lives and inflicted lifelong physical damage on many of the survivors. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Although the impact of the explosion depends on the power of the bomb and v\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
arious environmental conditions, let us see, based on the example of Nagasaki and Hiroshima, how the enormous power inside the atom, causing the deaths of hundreds of thousands of people in a few seconds, is released second by second: 
