standing within an area having a diameter of tens of kilometres. This flash is hundreds of times stronger than that emitted from the surface of the sun (per surface unit). The time elapsed since the outset of the explosion is so short that people close to
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 the explosion site cannot even find time to close their eyes. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 The pressure of the shock causes heavy damage indoors. Power transmission towers, two-piece bridges and skyscrapers built from glass-steel are also damaged. In the close surroundings of the exp\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
losion, a great amount of powder-like fine dust is raised. 
\par }{\b\f0\fs22\cf1\insrsid15550680 
\par }{\b\f0\fs22\cf1\insrsid3347702\charrsid14289276 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 \hich\f0 - 2 seconds after the explosion\'85}{\f0\fs22\cf1\insrsid3347702\charrsid14289276 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 The flashing mass and the air surrounding it form a fireball. The heat radiated from this fireball, whose surface is still extremely hot and which glows like the\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
