At this point, the shock wave hits the earth and causes the first mechanical damage. The wave creates powerful air pressure, the intensity of which decreases as one goes farther from the centre of the explosion. Even around 1.5 km away from this point, th
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 e\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  added pressure is twice as strong as normal atmospheric pressure. The chance of people staying alive at this pressure is 1%. 
\par }{\b\f0\fs22\cf1\insrsid15550680 
