\par }{\f0\fs22\cf1\insrsid3347702\charrsid14289276 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
Radiation consists of gamma rays, neutrons, electrons and similar sub-atomic particles moving at very high speeds such as 200,000 km per second. These particles may easily penetrate the human body and harm the cells for\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
ming the body. This damage may cause a fatal cancer or, if it takes place in reproductive cells, it may give rise to genetic disorders that will influence generations to come. Therefore, the results of a radioactive particle hitting a human being are very
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 serious. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Radiation released in atomic explosions affects living beings either directly or through the products of radioactive decay that emerge during the explosion. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 As one of these particles or rays travels at high speed in matter, it collides very stro\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
ngly with atoms or molecules that get in its way. This collision may be a disaster for the delicate structure of the cell. The cell may die, or, even if it recovers, it may start to grow in an uncontrolled fashion \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 
 which is cancer \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  perhaps weeks, months\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ,\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  or years later. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
Radiation is very intense in an area of 1,000 metres in diameter around the centre of the explosion. Those who survive other fatal factors lose almost all white cells in their blood, wounds appear on their skins, and all of them die becau
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
se of haemorrhages in a short period of time from a few days up to two or three weeks. The effect of radiation on those farther from the point of explosion varies. Those who are exposed to these harmful rays emitted by the fireball at distances of 13, 16,
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
and 22 km suffer from third, second, and first degree burns respectively. Digestive problems and haemorrhages are experienced less, but real disorders appear later: hair loss, skin burns, anaemia, sterility, miscarriages, giving birth to crippled or defor
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 m\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
ed babies. In these cases, too, death is possible within a period from ten days to three months. Even years later, sight disorders, leukaemia and radiation cancer may develop. One of the greatest dangers of hydrogen bomb explosions (another nuclear bomb o
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 f\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 enormous destructive power caused by the fusion of the nuclei of various hydrogen isotopes in the formation of helium nuclei) is the entrance of radioactive dust into the body through respiration, digestion and the skin. This dust causes the above-mentio
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 n\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ed disorders depending on the degree of contamination. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 All these are caused by atoms, which we cannot even see with our eyes. Atoms can form life just as they can destroy it. This property of the atom shows us very clearly how helpless we are and how supe
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 rior is Allah's power. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
With your body made up of atoms, you are breathing atoms in the air, eating atoms in food and drinking atoms of water. What you see is nothing other than the collision of electrons of the atoms in your eye with photons. And what abo
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ut what you feel by touch? The sensations are simply formed by atoms in your skin repelling atoms of objects. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Indeed, almost everyone knows today that his body, the universe, the world, in short, everything consists of atoms. Yet, perhaps, most people so \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
far never thought about what kind of a system the entity we call the atom has. Or, even if they did, they did not feel the need to investigate it, because they always thought this concerns physicists alone.}{\f0\fs22\cf1\insrsid14289276 
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  }{\f0\fs22\cf1\insrsid3347702\charrsid14289276 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Man, however, lives entwined within this perfect\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 system throughout his life. This is such a system that every one of the trillions of atoms forming the armchair on which we sit has an order about which a book could be written. It takes pages to tell the formation, the system and the power of a single a
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 t\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 om. As the technology advances and our knowledge of the universe increases, these pages also increase. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 How then did this order form? It cannot be that the atoms came into being by themselves in the wake of the Big Bang and then an appropriate environment \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
was formed by chance, and these atoms combined randomly to form the elements that comprised the universe. It is certainly impossible to explain such a system by "chance". Everything you see around you, and even the air you cannot see, consist of atoms, an
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 d\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  there is a very complex traffic between these atoms. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Who then can direct the traffic between the atoms? Can it be you? If you think that your body consists of atoms alone, then which one of your atoms directs which, and which atom directs what? Do the at
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 oms of your brain that are no different from other atoms control the others? If we assume that the atoms of your brain are directors, then we have to answer these questions:
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 * If all atoms forming the brain are directors, how and based on what do they make\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  their decisions? 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 * How do trillions of atoms forming the brain cooperate?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 * Why does not a single atom out of trillions of them oppose the decision that is taken?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 * How do the atoms communicate with each other?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Considering the above questions, it is obviously an illogical deduction to say that all of the trillions of atoms forming the brain are directors. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 So, can it be correct to think that only one of these trillions of atoms is the director and the others are \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
its followers? If we believe a single atom to be the director, then the questions that come to the mind are: 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 * Which atom is the director and who elected this atom?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 * Where in the brain is this atom?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 * What is the difference of this atom from the others?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 * Why do the other atoms obey this atom unconditionally?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Before answering these questions, let us state one more thing: the supposed director atom is also made up of other particles. Why and under what pretext do these particles come together to form this \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
director atom? Who controls these particles? Since there is another will directing these particles, how right would it be to defend that this atom is the director? 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 At this point, the claim that one of the atoms forming our brain may be the director atom i\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
s inevitably disproved. How do the countless number of atoms in the universe continue their existence in full harmony, while people, animals, plants, earth, air, water, objects, planets, space, and everything else are made of atoms? Which one of these cou
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 n\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
tless atoms can be the director when it itself is made up of many sub-particles? To make such a claim or to attribute everything to chance and to deny the being of Allah, Who created all the worlds, is only }{
\b\f0\fs22\cf1\insrsid3347702\charrsid14289276 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "rejecting those signs in iniquity and arrogance \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 in spite of their own certainty about them."}{\f0\fs22\cf1\insrsid3347702\charrsid14289276 
